♪ Danger, danger...

16:44.960 --> 16:46.960
Are you going to join in or what?

16:46.960 --> 16:47.960
♪ High voltage

16:47.960 --> 16:49.960
♪ When we touch

16:49.960 --> 16:51.320
♪ And when we kiss

16:51.320 --> 16:52.800
♪ Danger, danger...

16:52.800 --> 16:54.960
What!

16:54.960 --> 16:56.160
♪ High voltage

16:56.160 --> 16:57.960
♪ When we touch, when we kiss

16:57.960 --> 16:58.960
♪ When we touch... ♪

17:00.960 --> 17:03.960
- It's nothing.
- Are you sure?

17:03.960 --> 17:05.640
It's like having a tooth out.

17:05.640 --> 17:07.960
Men make more fuss over catching a cold.

17:07.960 --> 17:10.960
- Really?
- Don't worry yourself.

17:11.960 --> 17:13.960
Chloe, love, will you dig out that spare charger for me?

17:13.960 --> 17:16.640
Oh... Go on.

17:23.640 --> 17:25.960
Why are you feeding her nonsense?

17:25.960 --> 17:27.960
Men do overreact to colds.

17:27.960 --> 17:30.960
- You do.
- No! Playing down Jenny's cancer.

17:30.960 --> 17:32.960
Pretending it's no worse than an ingrowing toenail.

17:32.960 --> 17:35.960
I had one of those once. It was bloody painful.

17:36.960 --> 17:39.960
- She's worried, poor mite.
- I know she is!

17:39.960 --> 17:42.960
And I will reassure her. But not by making stuff up.

17:42.960 --> 17:44.800
I'm only trying to help.

17:44.800 --> 17:45.960
Leave the parenting to me.

17:45.960 --> 17:48.800
- I am her dad.
- And I'm her grandma!

17:48.800 --> 17:49.960
And if I can put a smile back on her face,

17:49.960 --> 17:51.960
then that's what I'm going to do.

17:54.960 --> 17:55.960
All right, love?

17:55.960 --> 17:57.640
Here you go. Thanks.

18:05.960 --> 18:07.960
Ellie!

18:07.960 --> 18:10.960
When are you going to start looking after your things!

18:10.960 --> 18:13.960
You're actually talking to yourself.

18:13.960 --> 18:16.960
Yeah, even when you're in the room! Look at the state of this place.

18:16.960 --> 18:19.000
Mum, I know you're upset about Jenny.

18:19.000 --> 18:20.960
- Is that what this is about?
- No!

18:20.960 --> 18:22.960
It's about the fact that your room's a bloody mess!

18:22.960 --> 18:25.960
All you can do is be there for her. Like me and Liv are here for you.

18:25.960 --> 18:28.960
Prove it, then. Tidy your room or the floordrobe gets it!

18:31.640 --> 18:33.960
I was going to get you flowers but then I thought,

18:33.960 --> 18:36.480
"Wise up, it's Jen."

18:36.480 --> 18:38.320
Oh!

18:38.320 --> 18:39.960
Thanks.

18:40.960 --> 18:42.960
You know me so well.

18:42.960 --> 18:43.960
Yes, I do.

18:44.960 --> 18:48.960
So, I've been, er, working on my "concerned" face.

18:48.960 --> 18:49.960
Oh, yeah?

18:52.960 --> 18:55.800
- How are you, Jen?
- I have had...

18:55.800 --> 18:58.800
..so much of that.

18:58.800 --> 19:02.640
Who knew there were so many sympathetic people in the world?

19:02.640 --> 19:04.960
And they've all been in touch.

19:04.960 --> 19:06.960
- Except David. 
- Oh, that'll be his way of dealing with it.

19:06.960 --> 19:08.960
- Denial.
- Mm.

19:08.960 --> 19:10.960
Literally, everybody's got an uplifting story

19:10.960 --> 19:12.960
about a friend who's survived cancer.

19:13.960 --> 19:14.960
How's Pete coping?

19:14.960 --> 19:18.960
By competing with my mum to see who can be the most caring.

19:18.960 --> 19:21.960
It's partly why I didn't want them to know.

19:21.960 --> 19:23.960
Can we please talk about something else?

19:23.960 --> 19:24.960
- Please...
- Yeah.

19:24.960 --> 19:27.960
- Oh, I've got a date tomorrow night.
- Oh, Tinder?

19:27.960 --> 19:30.960
No, no, a friend of Karen's. She set us up.

19:30.960 --> 19:33.960
- Does she not like this woman?
- Yeah, well, you have to wonder.

19:34.960 --> 19:36.960
She's never pushed me towards her pals before.

19:36.960 --> 19:37.960
Oi, oi.

19:37.960 --> 19:39.960
I hope you're not tiring her out.

19:39.960 --> 19:41.960
Oh, no, he's cheering me up.

19:41.960 --> 19:44.640
- Look, he brought me this.
- Oooh, nice.

19:44.640 --> 19:46.960
Well, you can have that when you're better.

19:46.960 --> 19:48.800
Oh, sod that. Let's have it now.

19:50.960 --> 19:52.960
Oh, have you fixed this?

19:53.960 --> 19:55.960
And there was me slagging you off.

19:55.960 --> 19:58.160
Aw...!

19:58.160 --> 19:59.960
Oh, thanks.

20:03.960 --> 20:06.960
Oh, hi. Hello again.

20:06.960 --> 20:08.960
I still want the bedsit, but there's a slight hitch.

20:08.960 --> 20:10.640
Have you brought the deposit?

20:10.640 --> 20:12.960
I didn't get the job. But there's another interview tomorrow.

20:12.960 --> 20:15.960
- So, if you can give me...
- Have you got the money, yes or no?

20:15.960 --> 20:16.960
..perhaps just another 24 hours?

20:17.960 --> 20:19.960
I'm sorry, but, erm...

20:19.960 --> 20:23.960
would you consider taking this as collateral?

20:23.960 --> 20:25.320
Er, it was given to me by my father.

20:30.960 --> 20:33.000
Did he used to holiday in Bangkok?

20:33.000 --> 20:35.960
- Hm?
- It looks like a fake to me.

20:56.960 --> 20:59.960
I was just on the phone to your sister. I gave her your news.

20:59.960 --> 21:01.960
It's two degrees in Winnipeg.

21:04.320 --> 21:07.960
- She was a bit upset.
- About the weather?

21:07.960 --> 21:09.960
Or has her Mountie boyfriend dumped her?

21:09.960 --> 21:12.160
He's offered to pay for her to fly home.

21:12.160 --> 21:14.320
Really?

21:14.320 --> 21:16.960
- I was joking.
- To help you convalesce.

21:16.960 --> 21:18.960
Oh, my God...!

21:18.960 --> 21:20.960
Breast cancer, I can cope with.

21:20.960 --> 21:22.960
But our Sheila...

21:22.960 --> 21:25.000
I told her we could manage.

21:25.000 --> 21:27.160
She said she'd pray instead.

21:27.160 --> 21:28.960
Brilliant.

21:29.960 --> 21:32.960
I remember buying you your first bra.

21:32.960 --> 21:34.000
You were ten.

21:34.000 --> 21:36.960
- We went to British Home Stores.
- Hm.

21:37.960 --> 21:40.960
We had sausage and chips in that horrible cafe.

21:43.960 --> 21:45.960
Are you worried about tomorrow?

21:47.960 --> 21:50.480
Yeah. I am a bit.

21:50.480 --> 21:52.320
Me, too.

21:53.960 --> 21:56.960
Oh, I wish I could swap places with you.

22:00.960 --> 22:02.960
Mum...

22:02.960 --> 22:05.800
I'm sorry I'm putting you through all this.

22:05.800 --> 22:06.960
Oh, it's not your fault, love.

22:06.960 --> 22:08.960
It's not great, though.

22:08.960 --> 22:11.800
At your age, I should be looking after you.

22:12.960 --> 22:15.960
Don't worry, love. Your turn will come.

22:36.710 --> 22:38.910
That's me. Thank you very much.

22:38.910 --> 22:40.710
Excusez-moi.

22:40.710 --> 22:41.710
Sorry.

22:43.710 --> 22:44.910
It's a clarion call.

22:44.910 --> 22:46.710
The voice of a generation.

22:46.710 --> 22:47.710
Oh, forget Delaney.

22:47.710 --> 22:49.910
This should be on the national curriculum.

22:51.550 --> 22:53.710
- Hey. 
- Oh, thank you very much.

22:54.710 --> 22:55.710
What do you think?

22:55.710 --> 22:58.710
Well, they could do with some more staff behind the bar.

22:58.710 --> 23:00.710
- The play. 
- Oh...

23:01.710 --> 23:02.710
It's a clarion call.

23:02.710 --> 23:04.710
The voice of a generation.

23:05.710 --> 23:07.710
- Oh, you think? 
- Oh, yeah.

23:07.710 --> 23:09.710
Oh. I mean, forget...

23:09.710 --> 23:12.710
..someone...

23:12.710 --> 23:14.710
This should be on the national curriculum.

23:14.710 --> 23:16.710
Oooh...

23:16.710 --> 23:18.710
- I think it's a load of old shit. 
- Really?

23:18.710 --> 23:20.710
Mm.

23:20.710 --> 23:22.710
Worse, it's poverty porn.

23:22.710 --> 23:24.710
No.

23:24.710 --> 23:26.070
And there's still another hour to go.

23:26.070 --> 23:27.710
Yes.

23:28.710 --> 23:30.710
- Pub? 
- Mm!

23:30.710 --> 23:31.710
Pub.

23:36.710 --> 23:37.710
So...

23:38.710 --> 23:40.710
- Here we are. 
- Oh, thank you.

23:41.710 --> 23:43.710
So, Karen's told me all about you.

23:43.710 --> 23:45.710
- Really? 
- Uh-uh.

23:45.710 --> 23:48.750
Relax. She gave you a clean bill of health.

23:48.750 --> 23:51.710
Oh, yeah, I've got all my medical certificates...

23:51.710 --> 23:54.710
- ..if you want to see them. 
- Upstairs, framed?

23:59.710 --> 24:02.710
In a bygone age, it'd be, er...etchings.

24:03.710 --> 24:05.710
So...

24:09.710 --> 24:11.710
- I'm, er, just...
- You're going to the toilet?

24:11.710 --> 24:13.710
- Yeah.
- Yes.

24:13.710 --> 24:15.710
Of course you are.

24:21.910 --> 24:24.710
You're asking my advice about women?

24:24.710 --> 24:26.550
Well, unless Jen's there.

24:27.710 --> 24:28.710
How are you?

24:29.750 --> 24:31.710
Go ahead, caller.

24:31.710 --> 24:33.710
I was just wondering whether he's a little shy?

24:33.710 --> 24:35.710
Adam?

24:35.710 --> 24:38.550
Believe me, I have heard many words to describe him,

24:38.550 --> 24:40.710
but shy is not one of them.

24:40.710 --> 24:42.710
- Maybe he just doesn't fancy me, then. 
- 'No, no, no, no.

24:42.710 --> 24:44.710
- 'That doesn't sound like him either.'
- Hm.

24:44.710 --> 24:47.710
It's just moving so fast, you know? Shite play, pub...

24:47.710 --> 24:48.710
'..back to mine.'

24:48.710 --> 24:50.750
Well, we're still waiting for an actual problem.

24:50.750 --> 24:53.750
- I'm not sure if I want to sleep with her.
- Do you not fancy her?

24:53.750 --> 24:55.710
'Have you met me? Of course I fancy her!'

24:55.710 --> 24:57.710
I mean, she's gorgeous, but...

24:57.710 --> 25:00.710
..you know, I don't want to be that bloke any more, into conquests.

25:00.710 --> 25:02.750
So, don't. 'But she's come back.'

25:02.750 --> 25:04.710
She might be expecting...

25:04.710 --> 25:07.550
I was up for this in the pub. I'm not sure about this now.

25:07.550 --> 25:10.710
Well, don't sleep with him. I'm sure he won't mind.

25:10.710 --> 25:12.230
I'm sorry about that.

25:12.230 --> 25:13.710
Hello?

25:13.710 --> 25:15.070
I took a little longer than I intended.

25:15.070 --> 25:16.710
- Number two?
- What?

25:16.710 --> 25:18.710
No, just, it was, erm...

25:18.710 --> 25:21.710
No, it was just a really long, er...wee.

25:22.710 --> 25:24.710
- Who's that?
- Your son?

25:24.710 --> 25:26.710
He's at a friend's tonight.

25:27.710 --> 25:29.710
Number fucking two!

25:29.710 --> 25:30.710
David!

25:30.710 --> 25:32.550
Yes. Come in.

25:32.550 --> 25:34.710
Thanks. I was driving past, saw the lights were on.

25:34.710 --> 25:36.390
No need to explain.

25:36.390 --> 25:37.710
- Erm... Come in, come in.
- Oh, thanks.

25:38.750 --> 25:41.710
Caitlin, this is David, a friend of mine.

25:41.710 --> 25:42.710
- Oh. Hi.
- I'm sorry.

25:42.710 --> 25:45.710
- I didn't know you had company. I'll be going.
-  No, no.

25:45.710 --> 25:47.710
Not on my account. No, stay and have a drink!

25:47.710 --> 25:49.230
- You don't mind, do you?
- No, I'm...

25:49.230 --> 25:51.390
I'm just going to finish that and I'll be on my way.

25:51.390 --> 25:53.390
Oh, well, don't mind if I do.

25:55.230 --> 25:56.910
Ah...

25:58.710 --> 26:00.710
You haven't got any whisky, have you?

26:12.710 --> 26:13.710
Pete?

26:14.710 --> 26:15.710
Pete...

26:19.710 --> 26:22.550
I don't want to turn the light off.

26:24.710 --> 26:27.070
It's the last time I'm going to go to sleep with a matching pair.

26:27.070 --> 26:28.710
Oh...

26:29.550 --> 26:31.550
Oh, you'll still be you, love.

26:32.710 --> 26:34.910
Would you mind giving me a hug, please?

26:35.750 --> 26:37.710
Of course.

27:16.550 --> 27:18.710
- Morning.
- Morning.

27:18.710 --> 27:21.710
- We tied one on last night, eh?
- Oh, yeah, couldn't have driven home.

27:21.710 --> 27:24.710
But, yeah, since Nikki's away, I hope I didn't cramp your style.

27:24.710 --> 27:26.390
No, no, that's fine.

27:26.390 --> 27:28.710
Oh, here, am I going to see you later?

27:28.710 --> 27:31.710
Oh, well, erm... Nikki's not back till tomorrow, so...

27:31.710 --> 27:34.390
- No, no. I mean, at the hospital.
- Hm?

27:34.390 --> 27:36.750
- Haven't you spoken to Pete? 
- Well, I saw I've got a message from him.

27:36.750 --> 27:40.070
- I haven't listened to him yet.
- Jenny's having her operation today.

27:41.710 --> 27:44.070
Jenny? What's wrong with her?

27:47.710 --> 27:49.710
Well, they don't give you much room, do they?

27:51.070 --> 27:52.710
- It's only one night.
- Excuse me.

27:52.710 --> 27:54.710
Is there somewhere my wife can hang her clothes up?

27:54.710 --> 27:56.070
Sorry, mate, that's it.

27:56.070 --> 27:57.910
- Really?
- He's just trying to be useful.

27:57.910 --> 27:59.710
Well, OK. Thanks anyway.

27:59.710 --> 28:02.550
Pete, I'm going to need chocolate.

28:02.550 --> 28:04.710
- Nil by mouth.
- For when I come round.

28:04.710 --> 28:07.710
Do you know what, I saw a vending machine in the corridor.

28:07.710 --> 28:10.710
Yeah. I mean, I'd go myself but...

28:11.710 --> 28:13.390
Great.

28:14.710 --> 28:17.710
Hi. Jennifer? Hello. I'm Dan.

28:17.710 --> 28:18.710
I'm the hospital chaplain.

28:19.710 --> 28:22.710
Christ, you haven't come to read my last rights, have ya?

28:22.710 --> 28:25.390
No, no. I'm, er, I'm doing my rounds.

28:25.390 --> 28:27.750
I'm a listening ear, if you ever need me.

28:29.710 --> 28:31.710
I don't. I've got family and friends for that, ta.

28:32.750 --> 28:34.910
- Well, you're one of the lucky ones.
- Lucky?

28:34.910 --> 28:37.390
I'm not in for my bunions, you know?

28:37.390 --> 28:38.710
I'm so sorry.

28:38.710 --> 28:40.710
- That was clumsy of me.
- Yeah.

28:40.710 --> 28:43.910
Yeah, you might want to work on that with your next customer.

28:45.230 --> 28:46.710
I hope everything goes well.

28:49.710 --> 28:51.710
That was a bit harsh, Jen.

28:53.710 --> 28:55.710
- He was just trying to be helpful.
- Hm.

28:55.710 --> 28:57.710
Everyone is.

28:57.710 --> 28:58.710
Did you get any?

28:58.710 --> 29:00.910
The machine ate my money.

29:04.710 --> 29:06.070
I don't get any benefits for 13 weeks?!

29:06.070 --> 29:09.710
- You did walk out of your last job, Mr Marsden.
-  On principle.

29:10.710 --> 29:13.710
Look, I go for interviews, I'm too experienced,

29:13.710 --> 29:16.550
too expensive, too old.

29:16.550 --> 29:18.390
Maybe I piss people off.

29:18.390 --> 29:20.710
Look, I've been sleeping in my car, for God's sake!

29:20.710 --> 29:23.710
- Any friends or family you can turn to? 
- I shouldn't have to!

29:23.710 --> 29:25.710
The amount of tax I've paid over the years...

29:25.710 --> 29:27.710
Maybe someone who could offer you a bed at least.

29:30.710 --> 29:33.710
Ah, David. What brings you here with a suitcase?

29:35.070 --> 29:36.710
This is so good of you, Adam.

29:36.710 --> 29:39.710
When you see me dressed like this, what do you think?

29:39.710 --> 29:42.070
How long's he going to stay this time?

29:42.070 --> 29:43.750
I can't ask them again.

29:44.750 --> 29:47.910
I'm sorry. Housing can tell you where to find the nearest hostels.

29:58.710 --> 29:59.710
No...

29:59.710 --> 30:00.710
No, that's my car!

30:02.230 --> 30:03.710
Excuse me!

30:05.710 --> 30:06.710
My...

30:07.710 --> 30:09.710
Oh, crap...!

30:11.710 --> 30:12.710
No.

30:14.070 --> 30:15.710
No...

30:22.070 --> 30:23.710
Bye.

30:23.710 --> 30:26.710
- I'll be waiting by your bed.
- No, you won't.

30:26.710 --> 30:28.710
- Adam's going to pick you up.
- Adam? Why?

30:28.710 --> 30:31.070
Cos you need a break, love. Seriously, go and have some fun.

30:32.710 --> 30:34.710
- Good luck.
- See you later.

30:37.710 --> 30:39.710
And get me chocolate!

30:42.710 --> 30:44.070
Love ya!

30:50.710 --> 30:51.710
Shit!

30:53.710 --> 30:55.710
Shit!

30:56.710 --> 30:59.390
- Everything all right?
- Oh...

30:59.390 --> 31:01.710
Erm, a temporary crisis of faith.

31:01.710 --> 31:04.710
Oh, cos the vending machine won't give you chocolate?

31:04.710 --> 31:07.710
Er, well, it was coffee. I think I pressed the wrong button.

31:07.710 --> 31:09.710
Well, I'm on my way to the canteen. Can I buy you one?

31:11.070 --> 31:12.710
Thank you.

31:13.710 --> 31:14.710
That's very kind of you.

31:15.710 --> 31:18.390
- Ta.
- Pleasure.

31:18.390 --> 31:19.710
So...

31:19.710 --> 31:21.710
So, after your friend sent me packing...

31:21.710 --> 31:24.710
- Yeah, I'm really sorry about that.
- Oh, that's OK.

31:25.710 --> 31:27.710
No, I was with a mum and dad

31:27.710 --> 31:31.230
as their eight-month-old was taken off his ventilator.

31:34.230 --> 31:38.550
And we'd made handprints and taken photos with the family.

31:38.550 --> 31:41.710
And we did everything we could to try and ease his passing,

31:41.710 --> 31:43.710
but sometimes the sheer weight of it just...

31:46.710 --> 31:48.710
And then...the vending machine.

31:49.750 --> 31:51.710
God... How do you keep the faith?

31:53.710 --> 31:55.710
By having faith to begin with.

31:56.910 --> 31:59.710
- You must be concerned about your friend.
-  Yeah, I am.

32:00.710 --> 32:03.710
But the stats are on her side. That's what I put my faith in.

32:03.710 --> 32:05.710
Sorry, I don't mean to belittle your belief.

32:05.710 --> 32:09.710
- It's just not something I share.
- Your stats suggest you wouldn't.

32:09.710 --> 32:11.910
Yeah.

32:13.710 --> 32:15.550
What is it you do?

32:15.550 --> 32:17.710
Publishing. Nothing useful.

32:18.710 --> 32:20.710
I used to try and make a difference,

32:20.710 --> 32:22.550
but now I just take old clothes to charity shops.

32:22.550 --> 32:24.710
And I haven't done that for a while, to be fair.

32:24.710 --> 32:27.710
Well, at the Mission, we're always grateful for donations.

32:27.710 --> 32:29.710
You'd be welcome any time.

32:35.230 --> 32:36.710
Oh...!

32:37.710 --> 32:40.390
I hate golf. Why would I want to practise it?

32:40.390 --> 32:41.710
Well...

32:41.710 --> 32:43.390
..so you can get better.

32:45.710 --> 32:48.710
Anyway, the point was to take your mind off Jen.

32:48.710 --> 32:50.710
It'll be two hours now.

32:50.710 --> 32:52.710
It'll be almost finished.

32:52.710 --> 32:53.710
Come on. Have another go. Come on.

32:53.710 --> 32:56.710
So, I want you to clear your mind of all thoughts.

32:56.710 --> 32:58.710
Focus solely on your swing.

33:00.710 --> 33:02.710
Oh... Were you listening to me?

33:02.710 --> 33:05.710
Yes, I was. I'm just crap, that's all!

33:06.710 --> 33:09.390
You know I'm hating this. You said.

33:10.710 --> 33:11.710
No, Jen's cancer.

33:13.710 --> 33:15.710
Oh, yeah, well...it can't be easy for you.

33:15.710 --> 33:19.710
I feel like a spare part. Come on, have another go.

33:19.710 --> 33:22.710
The doctors talk to Jenny in jargon that I don't understand.

33:22.710 --> 33:23.750
Come on.

33:25.710 --> 33:27.070
Hips!

33:27.910 --> 33:30.230
I just wish there was something I could do!

33:30.230 --> 33:32.710
Well, I'm sure your support is really important.

33:32.710 --> 33:34.710
